Cautionary Tale: Don’t assume randomization will always work

Sources of Sampling Error

  • Choosing 100 females for each pool
  • Prepping library & sequencing

Approach 1: Use known population to estimate expectations from randomly choosing 100 females for each pool

Approach 2: Randomize the illumina read labels (young & old) and recalculate differences in haplotype frequencies
